      "content": "it's everything. his half of the bed is just... cold. i go to make coffee and i realize i dont need two cups anymore. i look at the chair where he used to sit and it's like i'm looking at a void. i'm just going through the motions, eating, sleeping, breathing... but there's no point to any of it. it's like i'm already dead, just waiting for my body to catch up.",
